annotation.TEXT: Which of those four levels will it be? Vote now, and we'll find out next time!
Wait. I think I can open it anyway.
So... the pyramid is actually a castle?
Something... Something something.
Yeah, it looks like there could've been a secret exit somewhere in there, but I wouldn't know where to look. I'll probably take another look later.
Hey there Chuck! How's it... going? ...Okay, then.
Yeah, I totally wanted to fry that swooper while he was still hanging there... Although, maybe I should've saved that rainbow shell for flying?
Mushroom? No thanks.
I wonder what that pipe is for...
Oh, yeah. Look at those dotted blue blocks over that pipe. The Blue Switch must be in there!
Oh, joy. Phanto's decided to join us.
This guy again. I'm just gonna rush through this time.
Apparently, it's still football season in here. So, you a Giants fan or a Patriots fan?
Not that it was of any use, but at least I know what was in there now.
Well, it looks like I'll need a P-switch to get up there and reach the ON/OFF block.
Okay, I'm done here. Let's keep going.
Nuts. If only I had hit the Blue Switch...
No, Yoshi, I'm not losing you!
Yeah, I just thawed out a muncher. Now, it looks silver, but that may just be due to this level's palette, so it's probably a normal muncher.
Well, I do have a flower here, so here I go!
To be continued...
What's up here?
Yes, I have, but I'll probably want to come back this way again after I've hit a switch.
A spare cape is better than a spare nothing!
Looks like I'll need both fireballs and cape spins to get through here. I bet there's something good this way.
Yet another mushroom? Still no thanks. (Man, it really wants to give me mushrooms for some reason.)
There's just the Yellow Switch left to find, and I bet it's in world 5, but where? It looked to me like world 5 was almost done, unless there is indeed a secret exit in the pyramid...
In fact, I bet that message box said something like, "If you don't have a key, turn back now." ...or something.
And I still suck at hitting the goal tape!
Midpoint, and the P-switch! But, can I enter that pipe up there?
There's a key, but I'll need to find that switch first.
Alright, pyramid, here we go! (Sorry, but I don't have a fedora handy.)
Finishing world 5 also got 3 votes, but I want to go here next.
I probably had enough time to bring them both...
Push.
Yep, here's the passage.
Hey there baseball Chuck! You a Red Sox fan by any chance?
And I suck at hitting the goal tape, but at least I dodged the Phantos and finished the level!
Knowing this game, I'll probably still need the key later, so, out of the way, Phanto!
And there's yet another mushroom, and Phanto's here as well.
So I guess the second key was unimportant. I wonder if there was a secret exit somewhere in that level though...
Well, let's head back. I remember another passage near the beginning that was blocked by those switch blocks.
Nah, I'm good. I didn't even need the parakoopa to cross that gap.
You a splitter? Yeah, you're a splitter. No big deal. My cape can easily handle splitters!
Holy moley! (Okay, I should stop with those.)
...or I could enter 4-4, or 4-5...
This reminds me of the end of SMB3's 6-7, and if you didn't have a fire flower, you couldn't get enough coins to earn... an anchor. Yeah, no big loss if you missed that.
Well, there's the ON/OFF switch I was looking for.
I think this is the way I want to go.
Yeah, a blue koopa. The flight power it gives Yoshi is totally useful now!
Obviously, I'll need to hit a switch somewhere.
Well, that kinda worked.
At least dodging Phanto doesn't seem too difficult here.
Ooh, boy. That footballer is not placed in a nice position for me, but... I think I know a way to deal with him.
Okay, I guess we're making a mountain out of a mole hill... or something...
Oh, and a ghost house appears.
Note block jumps in a narrow passage with piranha plants in an ice cave... I imagine this wouldn't be nice if I didn't have a cape or Yoshi!
I see you, loose spikes!
It's an ice cave, but I don't know if it's a nice cave yet...
Guess what? It's time for another episode of Super SIG World 21! Let's take a look at the voting results...
Ah, so that's what that pipe is for. It's probably there in case you didn't have the key, which I'm guessing is required at some point.
I wonder if these guys are Yankees and Mets fans...
Yoshi, could you maybe stop getting hammered for a moment, please?
Whoa! Nearly collided with that Maverick!
Well, I could enter the ghost house next...
Ah, so that's what the key is for!
Well, I needed at least one key here... Oh, man! Two Phantos! Run!!!
Yoshi! Wow, good thing I hit that Blue Switch!
Yes! I managed to hit the goal tape this time! Whoo-hoo!
Just wanted to kill the dry bones from afar with a dive bomb.
Yeah! Got him!
Caution: Maverick Thwomp zone.
...or, I could go all the way over here and play 5-3.
Maybe I should've fast-forwarded this part...
Oh, no. I'm not losing Yoshi here!
Oh, I just saw something in the corner there. I'd better be careful about where I shoot my fireballs.
(Thanks to whoever it was who suggested that line over "piece of crap".)
Okay, so we've got these types of pipes...
Interestingly, this upper row of ice doesn't thaw out if hit with fire. It must just be acting like cement blocks or something.
Alright, that opened up 4-3, which managed to get a couple of votes even though it wasn't unlocked yet, so you know what? I'm going to play it now!
Yep, it's the Blue Switch!
Oh, this must be the "pyramid" part, complete with SMB2 music.
Alright, now I'm going over to 4-2 next, since that got 3 votes.
And that opened a path way up here to 4-5. But, I still have to get the other exit in that level!
Nope. That's probably where you come out of if you start the level from midpoint.
Can't enter from that side (unless maybe I had a key somehow).
Another key? Uhh... I could try to take both, but I'm just going to leave one behind. (I hope I don't regret that decision!)
And we've got Sledge Bros., with their own personal mole bodyguards!
PROTIP: That is not a way to get a lot of coins from a multi-coin block!
Another mushroom? No thanks again.
And now to head back and get the key.
Ow! Why you little fragment of excrement...
Alright, got the key, but, where do I use it?

1 vote for ⑨-⑥, 1 vote for world 174, 1 vote for 1-3, 1 vote for me to play Farmville, 3 votes for me to finish world 5, 1 vote for 4-4, 2 votes for 4-3, 3 votes for 4-2, and 8 votes for the pyramid (including 1 vote for me to optionally wear a fedora as I go in)!
Sure, fireballs may come in handy.
Wait, haven't I been this way already?
Also, I don't know why I delayed on the save prompt for so long...
-Something- Something! Dotted blue block something filled blue block something. Something!?
Push.
Careful! Good thing I had my cape equipped!
Luigifan22222's translation: "The person who does not have a key... The qualification to advance to this point should leave the few left upper drainpipe hurriedly."
Luigifan22222's translation: "-Switch Palace- It was good and found here! [] becomes [!] There seems to be it in other places!?" (Same as what the other switches say.)
